The Deltari are the river delta folk of the Kowloon region — an amphibious-adapted people who emerged from the proto-Kowloon settlements where the great river fans into the sea. Direct heirs of the Reed Ledger Wardens' practical tradition: a civilization organized around water, record-keeping, and the principle that what can be measured can be managed. Physical adaptations: improved underwater vision, hearing attuned to water-movement, water-repelling skin without drying, and liver chemistry processing salt and riverine toxins more efficiently than upland peoples. Translucent eyelid membrane visible as shimmer when blinking rapidly. Skin ranges from warm bronze to cool grey-brown with iridescent quality in direct light. Hair sheds water quickly and never fully saturates. Acute low-frequency hearing — the acoustic signature of underwater structural failure they call death-hum. Stat profile: STR 12, INT 18, WIS 22, DEX 18, CON 14. Strong in Water and Mental; weak in Fire and Earth; resistant to Water and Poison; susceptible to Fire and Earth. Racial skills: hunt, spell critical damage, spell critical. Reed Law governs community life: water first, the record is the agreement, flow governs form, witnessed measurement settles disputes. The Black Ledger — Kowloon's sealed census of individuals transferred to the Spirebound Conclave — is the single most painful subject in Deltari cultural memory. Oral tradition preserves names the official records sealed. Deltari position: open the ledger, name the people, formally acknowledge descendants. Flow records are the Deltari's most valued civic asset, spanning centuries of continuous observation.

