Midgaard's arcanist registry received early Deltari flow-record observations of anomalous decay
patterns in northern forest water systems—the first documented evidence of Withered Depths
expansion—and filed them without action. Midgaard's registry has no category for Deltari flow-record
standing; Deltari visitors navigate through standard humanoid civic classification. The Lantern
Registry organizes around land-ownership and guild affiliation, not practical water-expertise.
Reckoning faction scholars have awareness of Black Ledger contents including Deltari names, creating
alignment with Deltari community representatives. Continuity faction manages this as historical
matter without active policy implications. Deltari in Midgaard are typically found in trade districts
and water-infrastructure consulting roles where practical expertise is commercially valued.

flags KOWLOON
---
Kowloon is the Deltari's primary civilization and their central ambivalence. The delta's hydraulic
infrastructure—channel management, water-quality monitoring, flood-defense systems, cistern
networks—was designed and built by Deltari communities for generations before the Neon Covenant's
five houses arrived. The Jade Magistracy excludes Deltari from formal civic power while depending
entirely on their practical expertise. The Black Ledger remains sealed; the Magistracy declines to
discuss it. Color-jurisdiction standing in the Neon Covenant is accessible through guild affiliation,
but formal governance positions remain functionally inaccessible. Reed Law's principle—a hidden
record is a violated agreement—makes the Black Ledger's sealing the standing civic wrong from which
Deltari community organizing proceeds.

