A Deltari in Kowloon holds the most complete available record of the city that excludes them from
its governance. Flow records—maintained parallel to Jade Magistracy official documents—contain the
hydraulic history of every channel, cistern, and flood-defense system in the delta. The Magistracy
cannot suppress these records because it does not hold them. The Black Ledger's sealed status is the
most acute ongoing wrong: Deltari names transferred to the Conclave are preserved in oral tradition
by community mnemonists who have passed the list down across generations specifically because official
records were sealed. Reed Law is unambiguous: a sealed record is a violated agreement. Living in
Kowloon as a Deltari means inhabiting infrastructure you built while navigating governance structured
to exclude you from formal power over it.

